<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2621: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-17T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 17,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>13. Your telegram No. 32 of October 11, 9 a.m.</p>
                        <p>Department and the Navy Department both approve the wording of the
                            proclamation. You are authorized furthermore to determine the date of
                            the installation of the Provisional Government in accord with the
                            Military Governor.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>